<figureCitation box="[159,257,605,630]" captionStart-0="FIGURE 1" captionStart-1="FIGURE 2" captionStartId-0="2.[151,250,1753,1775]" captionStartId-1="3.[151,250,1982,2004]" captionTargetBox-0="[182,1410,674,1738]" captionTargetBox-1="[169,1417,1129,1961]" captionTargetId-0="figure@2.[182,1410,663,1738]" captionTargetId-1="figure@3.[169,1417,1129,1961]" captionTargetPageId-0="2" captionTargetPageId-1="3" captionText-0="FIGURE 1. A, South America, image derived from Natural Earth World physical map with shaded relief at 1.24 km resolution (http://www.naturalearthdata.com). B, Bolivia; study area indicated by black square. C, ecosystems of the Bolivian Yungas area; map derived from the shapefile of the biogeographical regionalization by Navarro &amp; Ferreira (2011), using the Geographic Information System QGIS 2.14 (available at http://www.qgis.org/en/site/); Collection location of holotype indicated by red point; MC, Montane humid Yungas forest of Coroico; MYC, Montane Yungas cloud forest of Coroico; MR, Montane Yungas rainforest; SE, Submontane evergreen South West Amazon forest; SSD, Submontane semi-deciduous Yungas forest of La Paz; SSE, Submontane seasonal evergreen Yungas forest. D, representative habitat of Macronemus waxrasapa sp. nov. E, holotype of M. waxrasapa sp. nov., live on beating sheet." captionText-1="FIGURE 2. Macronemus waxrasapa sp. nov., habitus: A, dorsal, including antennae; body without antennae: B, dorsal; C, ventral; D, lateral." httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/1439622/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/1439624/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="376">Figs 1–2</figureCitation>
