<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="379" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,151,861]" pageId="4" pageNumber="379">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,326,367,392]" pageId="4" pageNumber="379">Etymology</emphasis>
. The specific epithet, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Perger &amp; Santos-Silva" authorityYear="2018" box="[587,708,368,391]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Macronemus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="379" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="waxrasapa">waxrasapa</taxonomicName>
, means “the one that bears long horns” in Aymara, a language spoken by the Aymara people of the Bolivian and Peruvian Andes.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="379" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,151,861]" pageId="4" pageNumber="379">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,439,464]" pageId="4" pageNumber="379">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="Perger &amp; Santos-Silva, 2018" authorityName="Perger &amp; Santos-Silva" authorityYear="2018" box="[322,597,441,464]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Macronemus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="379" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="waxrasapa" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[322,597,441,464]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="379">Macronemus waxrasapa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[604,694,439,464]" pageId="4" pageNumber="379" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[604,694,439,464]" pageId="4" pageNumber="379">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
is separated from all congeners by the dark brown pubescent area extending to the distal third of the elytra. In all other species except of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Pascoe" baseAuthorityYear="1866" box="[991,1100,476,500]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Macronemus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="379" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="analis">
<emphasis box="[991,1100,476,500]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="379">M. analis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, this area is restricted to the anterior half of the elytra.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,151,861]" pageId="4" pageNumber="379">
Among the known species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1835" box="[531,676,549,572]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Macronemus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="379" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[531,676,549,572]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="379">Macronemus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Perger &amp; Santos-Silva, 2018" authorityName="Perger &amp; Santos-Silva" authorityYear="2018" box="[689,849,549,572]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Macronemus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="379" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="waxrasapa" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[689,849,549,572]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="379">M. waxrasapa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[856,945,548,573]" pageId="4" pageNumber="379" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[856,945,548,573]" pageId="4" pageNumber="379">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
is most similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Pascoe, 1866)" authorityName="Pascoe" authorityYear="1866" baseAuthorityName="Pascoe" baseAuthorityYear="1866" box="[1151,1431,548,573]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Macronemus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="379" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="analis">
<emphasis box="[1151,1257,548,572]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="379">M. analis</emphasis>
(Pascoe, 1866)
</taxonomicName>
, but can be distinguished by the character states shown in 
<tableCitation box="[793,877,583,608]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,239,908,931]" captionText="TABLE 1. Comparison of characters of Macronemus waxrasapa sp. nov. and M. analis (Pascoe, 1866)" pageId="4" pageNumber="379">Table 1</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,151,861]" pageId="4" pageNumber="379">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,674,620,645]" pageId="4" pageNumber="379">Geographic and ecological distribution.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Perger &amp; Santos-Silva, 2018" authorityName="Perger &amp; Santos-Silva" authorityYear="2018" box="[683,959,621,644]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Macronemus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="379" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="waxrasapa" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[683,959,621,644]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="379">Macronemus waxrasapa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[967,1058,620,645]" pageId="4" pageNumber="379" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[967,1058,620,645]" pageId="4" pageNumber="379">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
has been collected so far only in the area of Bolivian Yungas forest in 
<collectingRegion box="[565,774,655,680]" country="Bolivia" name="La Paz" pageId="4" pageNumber="379">La Paz department</collectingRegion>
(
<figureCitation box="[789,912,655,680]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1753,1775]" captionTargetBox="[182,1410,674,1738]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[182,1410,663,1738]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. A, South America, image derived from Natural Earth World physical map with shaded relief at 1.24 km resolution (http://www.naturalearthdata.com). B, Bolivia; study area indicated by black square. C, ecosystems of the Bolivian Yungas area; map derived from the shapefile of the biogeographical regionalization by Navarro &amp; Ferreira (2011), using the Geographic Information System QGIS 2.14 (available at http://www.qgis.org/en/site/); Collection location of holotype indicated by red point; MC, Montane humid Yungas forest of Coroico; MYC, Montane Yungas cloud forest of Coroico; MR, Montane Yungas rainforest; SE, Submontane evergreen South West Amazon forest; SSD, Submontane semi-deciduous Yungas forest of La Paz; SSE, Submontane seasonal evergreen Yungas forest. D, representative habitat of Macronemus waxrasapa sp. nov. E, holotype of M. waxrasapa sp. nov., live on beating sheet." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1439622/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="379">Fig. 1A–C</figureCitation>
). The mean annual rainfall in this mountainous area amounts to 
<quantity box="[338,554,692,717]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.85" metricValueMax="2.2" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="4" pageNumber="379" unit="mm" value="1850.0" valueMax="2200.0" valueMin="1500.0">1,500 to 2,200 mm</quantity>
with a mean annual temperature of 20°C (
<bibRefCitation pageId="4" pageNumber="379" refId="ref2744" refString="Molina-Carpio, J. (2005) Regimen de precipitacion en la cuenca de Huarinilla-Cotapata, La Paz-Bolivia. Ecologia en Bolivia, 40 (1), 43 - 55." type="journal article">Molina-Carpio 2005, data from the close by Huarinilla valley</bibRefCitation>
). According to the biogeographical regionalization by 
<bibRefCitation box="[1080,1387,727,752]" pageId="4" pageNumber="379" refId="ref2827" refString="Navarro, G. &amp; Ferreira, W. (2011) Mapa de Sistemas Ecologicos de Bolivia, escala 1: 250000. RUMBOL SRL-The Nature Conservancy (TNC), Bolivia. [Edicion CD-ROM]" type="journal article">Navarro &amp; Ferreira (2011)</bibRefCitation>
, the ecosystem in the study area is considered as submontane seasonal evergreen Yungas forest (
<figureCitation box="[1173,1259,764,789]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1753,1775]" captionTargetBox="[182,1410,674,1738]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[182,1410,663,1738]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. A, South America, image derived from Natural Earth World physical map with shaded relief at 1.24 km resolution (http://www.naturalearthdata.com). B, Bolivia; study area indicated by black square. C, ecosystems of the Bolivian Yungas area; map derived from the shapefile of the biogeographical regionalization by Navarro &amp; Ferreira (2011), using the Geographic Information System QGIS 2.14 (available at http://www.qgis.org/en/site/); Collection location of holotype indicated by red point; MC, Montane humid Yungas forest of Coroico; MYC, Montane Yungas cloud forest of Coroico; MR, Montane Yungas rainforest; SE, Submontane evergreen South West Amazon forest; SSD, Submontane semi-deciduous Yungas forest of La Paz; SSE, Submontane seasonal evergreen Yungas forest. D, representative habitat of Macronemus waxrasapa sp. nov. E, holotype of M. waxrasapa sp. nov., live on beating sheet." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1439622/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="379">Fig. 1B</figureCitation>
). Tree indicator species for this ecosystem are 
<taxonomicName authority="Buscalioni" authorityName="Buscalioni" box="[489,839,799,824]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Actinidiaceae" genus="Saurauia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="4" pageNumber="379" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="peruviana">
<emphasis box="[489,713,800,823]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="379">Saurauia peruviana</emphasis>
Buscalioni
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName box="[853,1011,799,824]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Actinidiaceae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="4" pageNumber="379" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Actinidiaceae</taxonomicName>
) and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dode" authorityYear="1909" box="[1072,1272,800,824]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Juglandaceae" genus="Juglans" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="4" pageNumber="379" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="boliviana">
<emphasis box="[1072,1272,800,824]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="379">Juglans boliviana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(C.DC.) Dode 1909 (
<taxonomicName authorityName="" authorityYear="1818" box="[221,374,836,861]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Juglandaceae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="4" pageNumber="379" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Juglandaceae</taxonomicName>
) (
<bibRefCitation box="[396,681,836,861]" pageId="4" pageNumber="379" refId="ref2827" refString="Navarro, G. &amp; Ferreira, W. (2011) Mapa de Sistemas Ecologicos de Bolivia, escala 1: 250000. RUMBOL SRL-The Nature Conservancy (TNC), Bolivia. [Edicion CD-ROM]" type="journal article">Navarro &amp; Ferreira 2011</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
