<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1783,1917]" pageId="4" pageNumber="379">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,260,1783,1808]" pageId="4" pageNumber="379">Remarks</emphasis>
. The beating tray sampling in a transect of 
<quantity box="[785,860,1784,1808]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="379" unit="m" value="300.0">300 m</quantity>
and with an effort of six hours during two days revealed 12 long-horned beetle species. Three of these species (25%), including 
<taxonomicName authority="Perger &amp; Santos-Silva, 2018" authorityName="Perger &amp; Santos-Silva" authorityYear="2018" box="[1056,1332,1821,1844]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Macronemus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="379" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="waxrasapa" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1056,1332,1821,1844]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="379">Macronemus waxrasapa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1339,1429,1820,1845]" pageId="4" pageNumber="379" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1339,1429,1820,1845]" pageId="4" pageNumber="379">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, were unknown to science, indicating the poor knowledge of the long-horned beetle fauna of this ecoregion and the high potential for the discovery of unknown taxa.
</paragraph>
